criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. HCC with at least one protocol defined risk factor, diagnosed confirmed by central
             pathological review and received R0 resection;

          2. BICR confirmed no resdual tumor lesions are detected in liver;

          3. Child-Puch score, Class A;

          4. ECOG score is 0;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients previously received PD-1 antibody, PD-L1 antibody, PD-L2 antibody or CTLA-4
             antibodies, including those who have participated in the JS001 clinical study;

          2. Portal vein tumor thrombi or liver metastases or recurrent liver cancer;

          3. With symptoms of central nervous system metastasis;

          4. With any history of active autoimmune disease or autoimmune disease;

          5. Known liver diseases with clinical significance;

          6. Patients infected by hepatitis B virus (HBV), hepatitis C virus (HCV), hepatitis D
             virus (HDV):

        Other protocol defined inclusion/exclusion criteria could apply
